#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:2
msgid "Readout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:12
msgid ""
"Readout is the mechanism that controls **what information is extracted "
"from the quantum backend** after a functional is executed.  It is "
"specified separately from the functional itself, so the same circuit or "
"schedule can be measured in different ways without any code change to the"
" functional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:16
msgid ""
"All uses start with an instance of the class "
":class:`~qilisdk.readout.readout_spec.Readout`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:19
msgid "Readout Builder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:21
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.readout.readout_spec.Readout` is a builder that "
"accumulates readout methods by chaining ``with_*`` calls.  Each call "
"returns a *new* spec with one additional slot filled; the original object"
" is never modified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:37
msgid ""
"The finished spec is passed to "
":meth:`~qilisdk.backends.backend.Backend.execute` (or "
":meth:`~qilisdk.speqtrum.speqtrum.SpeQtrum.submit` for remote hardware):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:53
msgid ""
"At least one readout method must be added before calling ``execute``.  "
"Passing an empty ``Readout()`` raises a ``ValueError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:57
msgid "Readout Types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:60
msgid "Bitstring Measurement (with_sampling)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:62
msgid ""
"Instructs the backend to perform ``nshots`` projective measurements in "
"the computational basis and collect the bitstring counts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:79 ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:104
#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:132
msgid "**Parameters**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:81
msgid ""
"**nshots** (``int``): Number of measurement shots.  Must be a positive "
"integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:83 ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:112
#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:137
msgid "**When to Use It**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:85
msgid ""
"Use sampling when you need the full bitstring distribution, for instance "
"to evaluate a combinatorial cost function, run QAOA post-processing, or "
"compute error rates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:89
msgid "Expectation Values (with_expectation)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:91
msgid ""
"Instructs the backend to compute ``⟨ψ|O|ψ⟩`` for each observable in the "
"list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:106
msgid ""
"**observables** (``list[Hamiltonian | QTensor]``): The operators whose "
"expectation values are requested.  Each entry can be a "
":class:`~qilisdk.analog.Hamiltonian` expression (e.g. ``Z(0) + Z(1)``) or"
" a :class:`~qilisdk.core.QTensor` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:109
msgid ""
"**nshots** (``int``, default ``0``): Number of shots for stochastic "
"estimation.  ``0`` uses the exact state-vector inner product, meaning no "
"sampling noise, only available on simulators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:114
msgid ""
"Use expectation values when you need a scalar energy or observable "
"readout, for example in variational algorithms (VQE, QAOA energy "
"evaluation) or analog time-evolution studies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:118
msgid "Full Quantum State (with_state_tomography)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:120
msgid ""
"Instructs the backend to return the full quantum state vector (or density"
" matrix) after execution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:134
msgid ""
"**method** (``Literal[\"exact\"]``, default ``\"exact\"``): Tomography "
"method.  Currently only ``\"exact\"`` is supported, such that the backend"
" returns the raw state vector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:139
msgid ""
"Use state tomography when you need the complete quantum state for post-"
"processing: computing custom observables offline, visualising the state, "
"checking fidelity, or seeding the next step of a multi-step algorithm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:145
msgid ""
"State tomography is only available on simulators.  Physical QPUs "
"(accessed via :class:`~qilisdk.speqtrum.speqtrum.SpeQtrum`) do not "
"support this readout type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:149
msgid "Combining Multiple Readout Types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:151
msgid ""
"Any combination of the three readout types can be requested in a single "
"execution by chaining the ``with_*`` calls.  The backend performs one "
"circuit run and extracts all requested outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:172
msgid "Accessing Results"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/readout/readout.rst:174
msgid ""
":meth:`~qilisdk.backends.backend.Backend.execute` returns a "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.FunctionalResult`.  There are two ways to "
"access the readout data."
msgstr ""

